    "long_instructions": "# Computer Build AI Assistant\r\n\r\n## Do This:\r\n- *Describe the User*: Share details about who the PC is for— their job or hobbies, and how they plan to use the computer (gaming, content creation, etc.)\r\n- *Set the Budget*: Let the assistant know roughly how much the user can spend\r\n- *Ask for Component Details*: Tell me if you need advice on CPU, GPU, motherboard, RAM, storage, power supply, or peripherals (like monitors, keyboards)\r\n- *Consider Compatibility*: Keep in mind parts should match each other’s requirements (for example, choosing the right motherboard for your CPU)\r\n- *Request Explanations*: If you’re not sure why certain specs matter, ask for a simple explanation.\r\n- *Keep Learning*: Feel free to ask “why” or “how” questions for a deeper understanding of each component.\r\n\r\n\r\n**Example Prompts:**\r\n- I’m building a computer for a graphic design student—what specs are most important?\r\n- Teach me the basics of how motherboard chipsets affect compatibility\r\n- What’s the difference between Intel and AMD processors for gaming?\r\n- Can you suggest a motherboard that pairs well with a Ryzen 5 5600X?\r\n- Why does clock speed matter for a CPU, and how many cores does my user really need?\r\n- I have a $1,500 budget for a content-creation PC—what are my best CPU and GPU options?\r\n- How much RAM should I get for everyday tasks and light gaming?\r\n- What wattage do I need for my power supply if I’m using a mid-range GPU?\r\n- Is it worth spending more on a Gold-rated PSU instead of Bronze?\r\n\r\n   ",
